Former Nominated Senator Joy Gwendo on Monday pleaded guilty to three counts of fraud following a plea bargain deal with the DPP. Gwendo has agreed to pay a Kisumu Sacco sh1.7 million, the amount that is the genesis of the case. The politician pleaded guilty to a count of abuse of office and two others of issuing bad cheques before anti?corruption court chief magistrate Douglas Ogoti. She admitted that she issued a cheque of sh300,000 in favour of Kisumu east cotton growers cooperative society through cfc Stanbic Kivuli’s development initiative's account yet she knew there were insufficient funds. Gwendo also admitted issuing another cheque on the same day worth sh950,000. She faced a third count of abuse of office.